{
  "texts": [
    "The spins of the physical states here all satisfy j i = 1 2, as expected in the minimal tension limit where only the bottom of the continuum survives.",
    "In [4,6], it was observed for the sl(2, R) k+2 WZW model in the RNS formalism that the spins must satisfy the constraintn i=1 j i = k + 2 2 (n + 2g -2) -(n + 3g -3),in order for a localising solution to covering maps to exist.",
    "At level k + 2 = 3, this was indeed satisfied by j i = 1 2 for all i.",
    "However, as discussed above, this approach is not well-defined in the k = 1 limit and we should instead apply the hybrid formalism which contains a sl(2, R) 1 ⊂ psu(1, 1|2) 1 current algebra.",
    "Therefore, we need to impose the above constraint at level k + 2 = 1 [7] n i=1j i = n 2 -(n -2 + 2g),(3.15)for non-vanishing correlation functions."
  ]
}